biography:
I am ring (রিং). Full name Shazedur Rahim Joardar. Started my computing in 1999. In 2005 achieved a Professional Diploma in Information Technology focusing Software Engineering from NIIT. I am an enthusiasts of GNU/Linux and Computing in my mother language, Bengali (বাংলা) .

In 2009 I had started working with some spinning mills here in Bangladesh as a Consultant, IT and MIS. In 2012 SFG IT department finally migrated with Free as in Freedom software only. In 2016 all the servers, desktop computers and laptops started running only on GNU/Linux distro. Ubuntu Server & Mint Desktop based solutions were deployed. Since October 2014 to December 2016 worked as an Adjunct Faculty member at Software Engineering Department in Daffodil International University at Dhaka, Bangladesh as I love to share my knowledge on Modern Operating Systems and Database among the pupils. Moreover I had frequently conducted various hardware and software hacking sessions and FOSS events for the pupils.

Besides my works I love to contribute to the society by helping people using GNU/Linux distributions and free software as a member of various Bengali and International forum sites.

I love to work hard to spread out GNU/Linux and Digital Freedom knowledge in our mother language (বাংলা/Bengali). I had sponsored and organized distro release parties, get together, seminars, barcamp and various types of technical and non-technical sessions on GNU, Linux Kernel, Debian, Ubuntu and Linux Mint in person and through voluntary organizations.

My email and telegram (https://t.me/toshazed) id are very public and open to all Digital Freedom enthusiasts, lovers, users and interested ones. I can communicate in Bengali, English, Hindi, Urdu and German. I also write frequently in my personal blog titled as রিং-দ্য ডন 'র ব্লগ on https://toshazed.wordpress.com.
